cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper discusses camera calibration and real-time video augmentation onto medical images, which are common topics in computer vision.
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper proposes a method to calibrate sensors attached to a mobile C-arm, which is a type of medical robot used in surgical procedures.
3. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper discusses the use of augmented reality in medical procedures, which involves the generation and display of computer graphics.
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of cameras and sensors to capture and process medical images and videos, which are common topics in multimedia research.
5. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper discusses the use of augmented reality in medical procedures, which involves the interaction between humans and computer systems.
